00:39.434 --> 00:41.768
Roses, a dozen.

00:41.770 --> 00:43.454
I know.

00:43.456 --> 00:45.739
He said he was heading to his
girlfriend's house

00:45.741 --> 00:47.241
and she cancelled on him.

00:47.243 --> 00:48.775
No, didn't even tell me
his name.

00:48.777 --> 00:50.744
Just said he didn't want them
to go to waste.

00:52.248 --> 00:53.464
It was nice.

00:53.466 --> 00:55.883
It's been a lousy week.

00:55.885 --> 00:58.585
Maybe things
are finally turning around.

01:01.574 --> 01:03.507
Tragic news out of Manhattan
this evening,

01:03.509 --> 01:06.744
where a young woman was pushed
in front of a subway train.

01:06.746 --> 01:08.762
Seriously, you guys have, like,

01:08.764 --> 01:09.980
the cutest
kids in New York.

01:09.982 --> 01:11.098
It's true.

01:12.101 --> 01:13.633
Who knew these
guys back in college

01:13.635 --> 01:15.602
would be
such a baby factory?

01:15.604 --> 01:17.070
Me, I did.

01:17.072 --> 01:19.323
Right after I caught
them having sex in my bed.

01:19.325 --> 01:20.441
One time, freshman year.

01:20.443 --> 01:21.575
You must move on.

01:21.577 --> 01:23.026
Yeah, and let's be honest,

01:23.028 --> 01:24.578
that is the most action that
bed saw all year.

01:24.580 --> 01:25.746
Ouch.

01:25.748 --> 01:27.614
Are you going
to be able to make it

01:27.616 --> 01:28.949
to Sammy's
birthday party on Saturday?

01:28.951 --> 01:30.451
2:00, yes.

01:30.453 --> 01:32.252
I am wrapping up
with my client on Friday

01:32.254 --> 01:34.338
and I may be able
to help and come set up.

01:34.340 --> 01:35.706
How is that going,
by the way?

01:35.708 --> 01:37.491
The companionship thing.

01:37.493 --> 01:40.043
If by "thing",
you mean career,

01:40.045 --> 01:42.045
it is going really well.

01:42.047 --> 01:45.466
I-I-I don't know, I've
worked with some amazing people.

01:45.468 --> 01:47.301
I think it's incredible,
what you're doing.

01:47.303 --> 01:49.186
I mean, you walk away from
being a doctor,

01:49.188 --> 01:50.670
find a new way to help people?

01:50.672 --> 01:52.272
Same old Jo.

01:52.274 --> 01:54.308
Sweet.

01:54.310 --> 01:55.309
To Joan.
To Joan.

01:55.311 --> 01:56.343
And the baby.

01:56.345 --> 01:59.530
And the baby!

02:02.485 --> 02:04.651
Oh, sorry, guys, this is,
um, one of the rehab facilities

02:04.653 --> 02:06.203
that, um, refers me
to other clients.

02:06.205 --> 02:07.354
I should take it.

02:07.356 --> 02:08.687
I'll be right back.

02:08.690 --> 02:11.825
This is Joan Watson.

02:11.827 --> 02:15.045
Joan, this is
Dr. Caruso at Hemdale.

02:15.047 --> 02:17.030
I sent you a case file
a little while ago.

02:17.032 --> 02:18.665
I was wondering if you had
a chance to look at it?

02:18.667 --> 02:21.251
I'm just opening it right now.

02:21.253 --> 02:22.803
The patient in question

02:22.805 --> 02:24.538
completes his stay with us
on Monday.

02:24.540 --> 02:27.374
His father expressed some
concerns about life post-rehab,

02:27.376 --> 02:29.977
so, I recommended a companion.

02:29.979 --> 02:32.179
He looked at some resumes
and chose you.

02:32.181 --> 02:35.265
So, can I tell him
the interest is mutual?

02:35.267 --> 02:37.651
Sure, I just have one question.

02:37.653 --> 02:39.853
Uh, what kind of name
is Sherlock?

03:14.473 --> 03:17.190
I can't do this.

03:17.192 --> 03:18.392
Ah, just shut it off.

03:20.262 --> 03:21.812
Can't let
the noise get to you.

03:21.814 --> 03:23.763
You know this.
I know.

03:23.765 --> 03:25.949
But you did better
with the lock this time.

03:25.951 --> 03:29.202
It only took you six seconds.

03:29.204 --> 03:30.770
How weird is this?

03:30.772 --> 03:31.872
You're Sherlock's sponsor

03:31.874 --> 03:33.490
and I'm his sober--

03:33.492 --> 03:36.076
well, I <i>was</i> his sober
companion-- until recently.

03:36.171 --> 03:38.872
And now you're teaching me
how to break into cars.

03:38.874 --> 03:41.090
You want to do
the kind of work he does.

03:41.092 --> 03:42.876
Besides, every hour
I spend with you,

03:42.878 --> 03:44.577
he's got to do two with me.

03:44.579 --> 03:46.045
How's that going?

03:46.047 --> 03:47.046
He's good.

03:47.048 --> 03:48.348
He's in a good place.

03:48.350 --> 03:50.216
Happier since you
decided to work with him.

03:54.922 --> 03:56.639
Hey, I gotta go.

03:56.641 --> 03:59.225
I'll give you a ride.

04:03.864 --> 04:05.198
Dreadful news:

04:05.200 --> 04:06.399
I heard from my father
this morning.

04:06.401 --> 04:07.567
Really?

04:07.569 --> 04:08.785
Not the man himself,
of course.

04:08.787 --> 04:10.320
One of his minions.

04:10.322 --> 04:12.104
Apparently, he's holding me
to the bargain

04:12.106 --> 04:14.123
that we struck when I borrowed
that pittance from him.

04:14.125 --> 04:16.075
If you're referring
to the $2.2 million

04:16.077 --> 04:18.611
that you borrowed to pay off
the kidnapping ransom,

04:18.613 --> 04:20.079
I'd say that's a
little more than a pittance.

04:20.081 --> 04:21.464
I foiled that kidnapper.

04:21.466 --> 04:22.799
Every penny was accounted for
and returned.

04:22.801 --> 04:24.116
Yeah, but still.

04:24.118 --> 04:25.301
You're off his teats now,
Watson,

04:25.303 --> 04:26.836
you can stop taking his side.

04:26.838 --> 04:28.454
What did he want?

04:28.456 --> 04:30.890
Uh, to meet with
one of his many attorneys

04:30.892 --> 04:34.477
this morning and discuss work
of an investigative nature.

04:34.479 --> 04:37.480
Knowing Father, the man
is a shyster's shyster.

04:37.482 --> 04:39.148
You know, Dad once
helped defending a client

04:39.150 --> 04:42.068
who was equal parts
Adolf Hitler and Bernie Madoff.

04:42.070 --> 04:43.987
Hey, does your father
know that I'm still here

04:43.989 --> 04:45.104
and that we're
working together now?

04:45.106 --> 04:46.356
Why would he care?

04:46.358 --> 04:47.774
I don't know,
I was just curious.

04:47.776 --> 04:49.659
You're an aspiring
detective now, Watson.

04:49.661 --> 04:52.144
Apply your
curiosity to your cases.

04:55.266 --> 04:56.599
Impressive.

04:56.601 --> 04:58.451
I know; I could look
at this all day.

04:58.453 --> 05:00.503
No, I was talking
about the glass.

05:00.505 --> 05:02.672
It's... bullet-proof.

05:02.674 --> 05:05.591
Six-inch glass-clad
polycarbonate, hmm.

05:05.953 --> 05:07.787
Mr. Holmes.

05:07.789 --> 05:09.372
Philip Armistead.

05:09.374 --> 05:10.522
Do you know that "shyster"

05:10.524 --> 05:13.909
is German for
"one who defecates"?

05:15.579 --> 05:17.463
And this is
my assistant Rebecca.

05:17.465 --> 05:19.749
So, let's cut to the proverbial
chase, shall we?

05:19.751 --> 05:21.467
How much slime
will my associate and I

05:21.469 --> 05:23.219
have to wade through in order
to help you?

05:23.221 --> 05:24.970
My father said you were
in need of my services.

05:24.972 --> 05:27.706
You're an attorney, you work
for him, he values you:

05:27.708 --> 05:29.141
three good reasons to assume

05:29.143 --> 05:31.227
that the work we will have to do
will be vile.

05:31.229 --> 05:35.481
Actually, I was hoping you
might be able to help Rebecca.

05:35.483 --> 05:37.183
My sister Callie...

05:37.185 --> 05:39.268
she went missing
almost six months ago.

05:39.270 --> 05:41.771
I'm worried her husband may
have done something to her.

05:44.391 --> 05:50.913
Uh, I guess I should start with
"I'm sorry."

05:50.915 --> 05:53.099
I hate that I can't say these
things to you face-to-face.

05:53.101 --> 05:54.367
It's just...

05:54.369 --> 05:59.839
I don't love you anymore, Drew.

05:59.841 --> 06:03.509
And it hurts to say that,
you don't know how much.

06:03.511 --> 06:07.012
I care about you,
I want you to be happy,

06:07.014 --> 06:09.882
but I need to be happy, too.

06:09.884 --> 06:11.517
And I thought that
I could tough it out

06:11.519 --> 06:14.053
and give us both
a little more time.

06:14.055 --> 06:16.856
But then that woman got pushed
in front of a subway train

06:16.858 --> 06:19.475
the other day-- the woman with
the flowers--

06:19.477 --> 06:22.528
and, I don't know, I couldn't
stop thinking about her.

06:22.530 --> 06:24.763
Life is too short
to stay with someone

06:24.765 --> 06:26.732
who doesn't make you happy.

06:26.734 --> 06:30.503
So, uh, I'm going to go away
for a little while.

06:30.505 --> 06:32.688
I don't know where and I-I don't
know for how long.

06:32.690 --> 06:34.457
I just know
that I need some time.

06:35.942 --> 06:37.293
Maybe, someday, you'll find it

06:37.295 --> 06:39.295
in your heart to forgive me.

06:41.248 --> 06:44.083
When my brother-in-law Drew
first showed me the video,

06:44.085 --> 06:45.551
I didn't question it.

06:45.553 --> 06:48.220
Callie had always
been a little fragile.

06:48.222 --> 06:50.389
Packing up her stuff
and hiding out for a while,

06:50.391 --> 06:51.957
that sounded like her.

06:51.959 --> 06:55.094
But then after the days started
turning into weeks,

06:55.096 --> 06:56.562
I got suspicious.

06:56.564 --> 06:58.681
The marriage
was... troubled?

06:58.683 --> 07:00.466
Callie had left him once before.

07:00.468 --> 07:01.517
That was about a
year and a half ago.

07:01.519 --> 07:03.018
What happened?

07:03.020 --> 07:05.187
I don't know.
Callie didn't even tell me

07:05.189 --> 07:06.605
she'd done it
till a few weeks later,

07:06.607 --> 07:08.140
and by then,
she and Drew were back together.

07:08.142 --> 07:10.526
And I tried to
get her to talk about it,

07:10.528 --> 07:12.811
but she said it
was all in the past.

07:12.813 --> 07:14.163
She was like that--

07:14.165 --> 07:15.915
she kept everything
bottled up; private.

07:15.917 --> 07:18.484
So, when she
didn't return my phone calls

07:18.486 --> 07:21.036
after Dr showed me the video,
I wasn't surprised.

07:21.038 --> 07:23.655
After a few weeks,
Rebecca went to the police.

07:23.657 --> 07:26.375
Th tried to locate
Callie via her cell phone,

07:26.377 --> 07:27.593
credit card,
e-mail records,

07:27.595 --> 07:29.512
but they came up empty.

07:29.514 --> 07:32.381
She hadn't used any of them
since before she disappeared.

07:32.383 --> 07:34.884
They questioned Drew, but
he managed to convince them

07:34.886 --> 07:36.218
the video was authentic.

07:36.220 --> 07:38.387
Oh, you-you
think it's a fake?

07:38.389 --> 07:41.440
I think things were bad between
Drew and my sister.

07:41.442 --> 07:43.225
He could've forced her
to make the video

07:43.227 --> 07:44.777
so that,
after he killed her,

07:44.779 --> 07:46.946
he could show it to the police
and convince them

07:46.948 --> 07:48.147
that she'd run away.

07:48.149 --> 07:49.482
Which he did.

07:49.484 --> 07:50.816
There's also the trunk.

07:52.819 --> 07:54.537
It was our grandmother's.

07:54.539 --> 07:57.689
My father willed
it to me before he died.

07:57.691 --> 07:59.325
My apartment
is tiny, so I let Callie

07:59.327 --> 08:00.543
keep it at her place.

08:00.545 --> 08:01.794
The deal was,

08:01.796 --> 08:04.079
she would give it
to me if I ever moved.

08:04.081 --> 08:05.548
The first time that I went

08:05.550 --> 08:07.216
to see Drew
after she disappeared,

08:07.218 --> 08:09.585
I realized that
the trunk was gone, too.

08:09.587 --> 08:11.136
He claimed that
she took it with her,

08:11.138 --> 08:12.721
but I know that
she would never do that.

08:12.723 --> 08:15.374
I told the police that I think
he did what he did.

08:15.376 --> 08:17.426
And he used the
trunk to get rid of her.

08:17.428 --> 08:18.727
I've had the firm's
top investigators

08:18.729 --> 08:20.312
on this for months.

08:20.314 --> 08:22.714
They haven't managed to
come up with anything.

08:22.716 --> 08:24.049
I happened to speak with
your father the other day,

08:24.051 --> 08:26.185
and he recommended
I reach out to you.

08:26.187 --> 08:28.270
Would you excuse us
for just one moment?

08:28.272 --> 08:30.022
Come on.

08:30.024 --> 08:31.690
That woman
could not be more wrong

08:31.692 --> 08:33.107
about her sister's video.

08:33.110 --> 08:35.277
It was most certainly
not made under duress.

08:35.279 --> 08:36.828
Tell me.

08:36.831 --> 08:38.581
The human face, Watson,
is like the penis.

08:38.582 --> 08:39.898
Or so said the great

08:39.900 --> 08:41.534
personality theorist
Silvan Tomkins.

08:41.535 --> 08:43.034
The point being:

08:43.037 --> 08:44.753
the face,
like the male member,

08:44.755 --> 08:46.589
has a mind of its own;
it betrays us

08:46.591 --> 08:49.908
on an almost daily basis;
advertises our secrets

08:49.910 --> 08:51.260
to those
who know that to look for.

08:51.262 --> 08:52.845
The woman in that video
was utterly calm

08:52.847 --> 08:54.380
when she filmed it.

08:54.382 --> 08:56.549
More than that, I think she was
excited to move on.

08:56.551 --> 08:58.851
You and I were not
looking at the same video.

08:58.853 --> 09:00.052
Her jaw muscles
were relaxed, not tight.

09:00.054 --> 09:01.353
Her nose wings
were not dilated.

09:01.355 --> 09:02.555
She wasn't going
off some script,

09:02.557 --> 09:04.223
she meant every
word she was saying.

09:04.225 --> 09:05.160
Nose wings.

09:05.185 --> 09:06.610
We have an opportunity
here, Watson.

09:06.611 --> 09:09.028
More precisely, you do.

09:09.030 --> 09:11.814
I think this would make
an excellent first case for you.

09:11.816 --> 09:14.650
You want me to find Callie
Burrell on my own?

09:14.652 --> 09:16.702
Every good investigator needs
to be able to find people

09:16.704 --> 09:18.237
who do not wish to be found.

09:18.239 --> 09:19.655
More often than not,
those are dangerous criminals.

09:19.657 --> 09:23.576
Ms. Burrell is merely a wife
grown tired of her husband.

09:23.578 --> 09:25.244
It's a case
with training wheels.

09:25.246 --> 09:27.046
You can't be sure
that Callie is okay.

09:27.048 --> 09:28.614
And, you know what,
th-th-there might be something

09:28.616 --> 09:30.049
to what her sister is saying.

09:30.051 --> 09:33.285
Maybe, maybe not.
Your job to find out.

09:33.287 --> 09:35.721
Is this because the case
came through your father?

09:35.723 --> 09:38.457
No, it's because the case
suits you.

09:38.459 --> 09:41.960
Besides, I have one of my own
which I wish to take up.

09:43.647 --> 09:45.797
Oh, that's the woman that Callie
mentioned in her video.

09:45.799 --> 09:48.150
She was murdered
just days before Callie

09:48.152 --> 09:50.402
quote-unquote vanished.

09:50.404 --> 09:52.104
The man who pushed her
was never found.

09:52.106 --> 09:54.490
I lost a valued informant
to a pusher back in London

09:54.492 --> 09:56.609
Ugly business, yeah.

09:56.611 --> 09:58.410
As horrific a death
as you can imagine.

09:58.412 --> 10:00.079
Now, I found that killer.

10:00.081 --> 10:02.498
I suspect I can
find this one as well.

10:02.500 --> 10:04.500
Hey, aren't
you going to tell

10:04.502 --> 10:06.168
your father's friend what we're doing?
Your case now, Watson.

10:06.170 --> 10:07.486
You tell him.

10:07.511 --> 10:11.511
